No people of color are\ncoming to your play.
So it was like, basically,\nthe word we got from everybody
was no one's coming.
So of course, we took\nthat into our hearts.
And we said, well, then we\ndefinitely should do it.
But we did.
And what was amazing was we had\na very heterogeneous audience.
And it broke down a lot of\nspace around race and class
that really stuck with\nme, because as we all
know, finding spaces that\nare truly mixed race,
mixed class are rare in our\nvery racialized society.
And finding space\nto produce that is
